#. type: Title =
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Document organization"
msgstr "Organització del document"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:8
msgid "This Guide contains a series of guidelines that we have divided into:"
msgstr "Aquesta guia consta d’un seguit de directrius que hem dividit en:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Measures* that must be adopted and implemented in all projects.\n"
msgstr ""
"*Mesures* que han de ser adoptades i implementades en tots els projectes.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:12
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Recommendations* that do not have to be followed but which could be useful "
"in certain situations.\n"
msgstr ""
"*Recomanacions* que no és obligatori aplicar, però que poden ser d’utilitat "
"en determinades situacions.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:14
msgid ""
"Project managers are responsible for checking whether the measures are being "
"implemented properly and deciding which recommendations to follow."
msgstr ""
"És responsabilitat dels i les cap de projecte validar si les mesures s’estan "
"implementant correctament, i decidir quines recomanacions cal aplicar."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:16
msgid ""
"Some measures are sufficiently complex to merit being broken down into *sub-"
"measures* that can be individually validated."
msgstr ""
"Algunes mesures son prou complexes com per merèixer ser fraccionades en *sub-"
"mesures* que puguin ser validades individualment."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:19
msgid ""
"Some are impossible to adopt in certain projects, so in those cases we have "
"tried to offer some *alternatives* (guidelines that will be tagged as such "
"throughout the guide).  Each measure and its sub-measures are interlinked."
msgstr ""
"Algunes mesures son impossibles d’aplicar en determinats projectes, i en "
"aquest cas s’intenta donar algunes *alternatives* (directrius que es troben "
"etiquetades d’aquesta manera al llarg del document). Cada mesura i les seves "
"potencials alternatives es troben mútuament enllaçades."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:21
msgid "Each measure, recommendation or alternative consists of:"
msgstr "Cada mesura, recomanació o alternativa consta de:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:23
msgid "A unique identifier throughout the document."
msgstr "Un identificador únic per a tot el document."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:24
msgid "A list of tags."
msgstr "Un llistat d’etiquetes."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:27
msgid ""
"The *tags* help to restrict when and in what types of projects each measure "
"and recommendation are important.  For example, they can serve to generate a "
"checklist of things that project management needs to check."
msgstr ""
"Les *etiquetes* ajuden a restringir en quins moments i en quins tipus de "
"projecte son importants cada mesura i cada recomanació. Poden servir, per "
"exemple, per generar un checklist de coses que la direcció del projecte "
"necessita comprovar."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:30
msgid ""
"This chapter explains which type of tags are used throughout the guide.  The "
"other chapters set out the measures and recommendations by subject areas and "
"provide some necessary context for understanding the relevance of each "
"measure."
msgstr ""
"Els apartats d’aquest capítol expliquen els tipus d’etiquetes que es fan "
"servir al llarg de la Guia. La resta de capítols d’aquesta guia ordenen les "
"mesures i recomanacions en àrees temàtiques i donen el context necessari per "
"entendre la rellevància de cada mesura."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:32
msgid ""
"In the [Annex: Lists of measure and recommendations by tag] you will find "
"various lists of measures and recommendations classified by tags."
msgstr ""
"A l”[Annex: Llistats de mesures i recomanacions per etiquetes] es poden "
"trobar diferents llistats de mesures i recomanacions categoritzats per "
"etiquetes."

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:33
#, no-wrap
msgid "Use-case tags"
msgstr "Etiquetes per escenaris d’ús"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:37
msgid ""
"In this section we define the different situations or *use-cases* that can "
"arise in technological projects in relation to the free software components "
"they are based on.  These Use-Cases then determine which measures and "
"recommendations affect each project."
msgstr ""
"En aquest apartat es defineixen diferents situacions o *escenaris* que es "
"poden produir en els projectes tecnològics en relació als components de "
"programari lliure i de codi obert en els que es basen. Aquests escenaris "
"determinen després quines mesures i recomanacions afecten a cada projecte."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:43
msgid ""
"Each *project* defines an information system, and each system has a certain "
"number of software *components*.  Some components are distinguished from the "
"rest because each component has its own source code *repository*.  "
"(Occasionally we find complex components whose code, for practical reasons, "
"is shared between different repositories which are tagged and distributed "
"jointly).  The different components in a particular system can be run on the "
"same equipment or be distributed between different machines.  Likewise, they "
"may operate as part of the same process or various processes."
msgstr ""
"Cada *projecte* defineix un sistema d’informació, i cada sistema "
"d’informació consta d’una determinada quantitat de *components* de "
"programari. Uns components es distingeixen dels altres perquè cada component "
"té el seu propi *repositori* de codi font. (Ocasionalment trobem components "
"complexes que, per raons pràctiques, tenen el seu codi repartit en diferents "
"repositoris que es versionen i distribueixen coordinadament). Els diferents "
"components d’un determinat sistema poden executar-se tots en una mateixa "
"màquina, o bé poden trobar-se distribuïts en diferents màquines. També poden "
"executar-se com a part del mateix procés o en processos diversos."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:45
msgid "The following use-cases are contemplated:"
msgstr "Els escenaris contemplats son els següents:"

#. type: Table
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:68
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Tag\n"
"| Description\n"
"\n"
"| `Integration`\n"
"| *Integrate existing components*: it is necessary to install a new system "
"that can be built on the basis of existing components.\n"
"\n"
"| `Adaptation`\n"
"| *Modify an external component*: feature needs to be added to a component "
"that is already available, or it needs to be improved by solving defects, "
"adding translations, etc.\n"
"\n"
"| `Plugin`\n"
"| *Expand a platform with plugins*: new components need to be created that "
"can be integrated into a platform or framework already available and which "
"facilitates this task.\n"
"\n"
"| `NewProduct`\n"
"| *Create a new component*: a new solution needs to be created from scratch.\n"
"\n"
"| `Publication`\n"
"| *Publish code from an existing own component*: we have our own code, "
"developed under previous contracts and never publicly distributed, and we "
"want to make it available in a public repository, under a free software "
"license.\n"
"\n"
"| `Document`\n"
"| *Publish documents not linked to a single project*: we have documentation "
"that is not directly linked to a piece of software but we want to make it "
"freely available in a public repository.\n"
msgstr ""
"| Tag\n"
"| Descripció\n"
"\n"
"| `Integració`\n"
"| *Integrar components existents*: és necessari instalar un nou sistema que "
"es pot construir en base a components ja existents.\n"
"\n"
"| `Adaptació`\n"
"| *Modificar un component extern*: cal afegir funcionalitat a un component "
"ja disponible, o bé millorar-lo solucionant deficiències, afegint "
"traduccions, etc.\n"
"\n"
"| `Plugin`\n"
"| *Estendre una plataforma amb components endollables*: es requereix crear "
"nous components que s’integrin en una plataforma o framework ja disponible i "
"que facilita aquesta tasca.\n"
"\n"
"| `NouProducte`\n"
"| *Crear un component nou*: es necessita crear una solució nova des de zero.\n"
"\n"
"| `Publicació`\n"
"| *Publicar codi d’un component propi ja existent*: es disposa d’un codi "
"propi desenvolupat sota contractes anteriors i que mai ha estat publicat, i "
"es vol alliberar en un repositori públic.\n"
"\n"
"| `Document`\n"
"| *Publicar documentació no vinculada a un únic projecte*: es disposa d’una "
"documentació no directament vinculada a codi però que es vol alliberar en un "
"repositori públic.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:72
msgid ""
"All the Use-Cases, except the `Integration` and `Document` Use-Cases, refer "
"to a single software component.  This means different Use-Cases can coincide "
"in the same project if different components are affected in a different way."
msgstr ""
"Tots els escenaris, a excepció dels escenaris `Integració` i `Document`, fan "
"referència a un únic component de programari. Per tant, en un mateix "
"projecte poden concórrer diferents escenaris si components diferents es "
"troben afectats de diferent manera."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:74
msgid ""
"We exclude from the analysis contributions to projects that do not involve "
"modifying the code of a component, or creating a repository, such as "
"contributions to documenting or facilitating the adoption of certain tools "
"by third parties."
msgstr ""
"Deixem fora de l’anàlisi contribucions a projectes que no impliquen una "
"modificació del codi d’un component, o la creació d’un repositori, com poden "
"ser contribucions a la documentació o facilitació de l’adopció de certes "
"eines per part de tercers."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:76
msgid ""
"The `Integration`, `Adaptation`, `Plugin` and `NewProduct` use-cases may "
"occasionally require a *migration*, if we find ourselves in a situation of "
"implementing a system that partially or totally replaces the functions of a "
"previous system."
msgstr ""
"Els escenaris `Integració`, `Adaptació`, `Plugin` i ' NouProducte` poden "
"opcionalment requerir una *migració*, en cas que ens trobem en la situació "
"d’implantar un sistema que substitueix, en part o totalment, les funcions "
"d’un sistema anterior."

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:78
#, no-wrap
msgid "`Integration` Use-Case"
msgstr "Escenari `Integració`"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:81
msgid ""
"This Use-Case may involve creating one or more own repositories, not to "
"manage the code of any software _per se_ but to:"
msgstr ""
"Aquest escenari pot comportar la creació d’un o més repositoris propis, però "
"no per guardar-hi el codi de cap aplicació _pròpiament_, sinó per:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:83
msgid "Link it to project management tools such as issue managers."
msgstr ""
"Vincular-hi eines de gestió de projectes tals com gestors d’incidències"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:84
msgid "Save and link documents relating to using and operating the system"
msgstr ""
"Guardar o enllaçar documentació associada amb l’ús i operació del sistema"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:85
msgid ""
"Save configuration files and scripts necessary for deploying the system"
msgstr ""
"Guardar fitxers de configuració i scripts necessaris per al desplegament del "
"sistema"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:86
msgid ""
"Save configuration files and scripts necessary for running testing and "
"continuous integration environments, including _virtualisation_ and "
"_containerisation_"
msgstr ""
"Guardar fitxers de configuració i scripts necessaris per executar entorns de "
"prova i d’integració continua, incloent _virtualització_ i "
"_containerització_"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:87
msgid "Save system design and customisation features"
msgstr "Guardar elements de disseny i personalització del sistema"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:88
msgid "Save instructions for installing and using the system"
msgstr "Guardar instruccions d’instal·lació i ús del sistema"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:89
msgid "Save integration tests of the various components"
msgstr "Guardar tests d’integració dels diferents components"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:92
msgid ""
"With regard to customisation elements, we highlight the need for "
"*translating* user interface texts and other aspects of localisation and "
"internationalisation (l10n, i18n).  We contemplate two possibilities:"
msgstr ""
"En quant als elements de personalització, destaquem la *traducció* dels "
"literals que es mostren a l’usuari i d’altres aspectes de la localització i "
"internacionalització (l10n, i18n). Contemplem dues possibilitats:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:95
msgid ""
"The following conditions are met: (1) the software to be translated is "
"designed to incorporate translations of the interface, and (2) the "
"translations to be carried out may be of general interest to other potential "
"users of the tool.  In this case, we will try to fit the translations into "
"the original project, which means we would find ourselves in the <<use-case-"
"adaptation, Adaptation Use-Case>>."
msgstr ""
"Es compleixen les següents dues condicions: (1) el programari a traduir està "
"dissenyat per incorporar traduccions de la interfície, i (2) les traduccions "
"a realitzar poden ser d’utilitat general per a d’altres potencials usuaris "
"de l’eina. En aquest cas s’intentarà contribuir aquestes traduccions al "
"projecte original i per tant ens trobaríem en l'<<use-case-adaptation, "
"Escenari Adaptació>>."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:96
msgid ""
"One of the two conditions mentioned above is not met: we store the files "
"needed for doing the translation in an own repository."
msgstr ""
"Alguna de les dues condicions anteriors no es compleix i emmagatzemem els "
"fitxers necessaris per efectuar la traducció a un repositori propi."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:98
#, no-wrap
msgid "Wordpress"
msgstr "Wordpress"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:101
msgid ""
"A hypothetical example would be a web portal built using a content "
"management system such as Wordpress, with a MariaDB database."
msgstr ""
"Un exemple hipotètic seria un portal web construït utilitzant un gestor de "
"continguts com Wordpress, amb una base de dades MariaDB."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:104
msgid ""
"These are standard free software components but to make managing them "
"easier, it might be useful to save customised elements such as CSS files or "
"a list of Wordpress extensions to be uploaded in a repository, along with "
"Docker images that include all the necessary elements for its deployment."
msgstr ""
"Es tracta de components estàndard de programari lliure, però per facilitar-"
"ne la gestió pot convenir guardar en un repositori elements de "
"personalització com plantilles, fitxers CSS, imatges, llistat d’extensions "
"de Wordpress a carregar, així com imatges de Docker que incloguin tots els "
"elements necessaris per al desplegament."

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:106
#, no-wrap
msgid "`Adaptation` Use-Case"
msgstr "Escenari `Adaptació`"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:111
msgid ""
"This use-case might involve creating one or more own repositories with the "
"same contents described for the <<use-case-integration, Integration Use-"
"Case>>.  A distinctive feature of this use-case, however, is that Barcelona "
"City Council is sponsoring the development of a significant contribution to "
"a free software product that could potentially be incorporated into the "
"original product (even if this integration does not take place while it is "
"being developed).  These contributions must take the form of a series of "
"commits in a repository linked in some way to that of the original product."
msgstr ""
"Aquest escenari pot comportar la creació d’un o més repositoris propis amb "
"els mateixos continguts descrits per a l'<<use-case-integration, Escenari "
"Integració>>. En canvi, el tret distintiu d’aquest escenari és el patrocini "
"per part de l’Ajuntament de Barcelona del desenvolupament d’alguna "
"contribució significativa a un producte de programari lliure que pugui ser "
"potencialment incorporada al producte original (encara que aquesta "
"integració no es realitzi mentre dura el propi desenvolupament). Aquestes "
"contribucions han de materialitzar-se en un conjunt de _commits_ en un "
"repositori que estigui vinculat d’alguna manera al repositori del producte "
"original."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:113
msgid "There may be various types of contributions:"
msgstr "Les contribucions poden ser de diversa naturalesa:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:115
msgid ""
"New features that Barcelona City Council needs and which could be of "
"interest to other entities or users"
msgstr ""
"Noves funcionalitats que l’Ajuntament de Barcelona necessita i que poden ser "
"d’interès per a més entitats o usuaris"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:116
msgid ""
"Complete translations (or significant coverage) of the user interface, as "
"well as other localisation (l10n) and internationalisation (i18n) "
"improvements that might be of general use to other potential users of the "
"tool."
msgstr ""
"Traduccions complertes (o amb una cobertura significativa) de la interfície "
"d’usuari, així com altres millores de localització (l10n) i "
"internacionalització (i18n) que poden ser d’utilitat general per a d’altres "
"potencials usuaris de l’eina."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:118
msgid ""
"If the translations and localisation elements are mixed with the City "
"Council's own customised elements, or if the original product is not "
"designed to incorporate new translations and localisations, then it is not "
"possible to plan a contribution like this because we would be in the <<use-"
"case-integration, Integration Use-case>>."
msgstr ""
"Si les traduccions o elements de localització es troben barrejats amb "
"elements de personalització propis de l’Ajuntament, o bé el producte "
"original no està dissenyat per incorporar noves traduccions i "
"localitzacions, aleshores no es pot plantejar una contribució com a tal i "
"ens trobaríem a l'<<use-case-integration, Escenari Integració>>."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:120
#, no-wrap
msgid "Barcelona City Council's ethical mail box"
msgstr "Bústia ètica de l'Ajuntament de Barcelona"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:124
msgid ""
"There was an original piece of software, that of https://www.globaleaks.org/"
"[Globaleaks], and the features of generating an internal file and sending a "
"reply to the user in the form of a PDF were incorporated into that.  These "
"features are now part of the https://github.com/globaleaks/"
"GlobaLeaks[Globaleaks main repository]’s master branch."
msgstr ""
"Existia un programari original, el de https://www.globaleaks.org/"
"[Globaleaks], al qual se li han incorporat les funcionalitats de generació "
"d’expedient intern i de devolució de resposta a l’usuari en forma de PDF. "
"Aquestes funcionalitats formen part ara mateix de la branca master del https:"
"//github.com/globaleaks/GlobaLeaks[repositori principal de Globaleaks]."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:127
msgid ""
"Customisation tasks have been carried out in the same project, including the "
"translation of the interface into Catalan, but as some user texts are not "
"for general use but instead are the City Council's own customisations, it "
"has not been possible to contribute the translation itself to the original "
"project."
msgstr ""
"En el mateix projecte s’han desenvolupat tasques de personalització, "
"incloent la traducció de la interfície al català, però com que alguns "
"literals no son d’ús general sinó que son personalitzacions pròpies de "
"l’Ajuntament, la traducció en sí no s’ha pogut contribuir al projecte "
"original."

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:129
#, no-wrap
msgid "`Plugin` Use-case"
msgstr "Escenari `Plugin`"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:132
msgid ""
"This is a use-case half way between integrating new features into an already "
"existing product (<<use-case-adaptation, Adaptation Use-case>>) and "
"developing a new product (<<use-case-new-product, NewProduct Use-case>>), "
"and it shares features of both."
msgstr ""
"Es tracta d’un escenari intermig entre la integració de funcionalitats noves "
"a un producte ja existent (<<use-case-adaptation, Escenari Adaptació>>) i el "
"desenvolupament d’un nou producte (<<use-case-new-product, Escenari Nou "
"Producte>>) i comparteix característiques dels dos."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:136
msgid ""
"On the one hand, it starts with an existing piece of software to which a "
"feature has to be added.  On the other hand, the software architecture is "
"modular and provides for extension by means of a standardised mechanism that "
"enables semi-independent development of the new modules in such a way that "
"some aspects are quite similar to a new product.  In particular, the new "
"modules have their own repository (which is not a copy of the original "
"product's repository) and the releases are not linked to those of the "
"framework product."
msgstr ""
"D'una banda, es parteix d’un programari ja existent al qual s’ha d’afegir "
"funcionalitat. De l’altre, l’arquitectura d’aquest programari és modular i "
"preveu l’extensió mitjançant un mecanisme estandaritzat que permet una "
"evolució semi-independent dels nous mòduls, de tal manera que en alguns "
"aspectes s’assemblen bastant a un producte nou. En particular, els nous "
"mòduls tenen el seu repositori propi (que no és una còpia del repositori del "
"producte original), i les entregues estan desvinculades de les del producte "
"marc."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:138
#, no-wrap
msgid "Open Data Barcelona"
msgstr "Open Data Barcelona"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:142
msgid ""
"The http://opendata-ajuntament.barcelona.cat/[City Council's open data "
"portal] is based on https://ckan.org/[CKAN] open data portal software.  This "
"product is http://docs.ckan.org/en/latest/extensions/plugin-interfaces."
"html[easily extendible] by means of plugins or extensions and when the new "
"portal was being developed it was necessary to modify an existing plugin "
"(which would also correspond to the <<use-case-adaptation, Adaptation Use-"
"case>>) as well as create new ones."
msgstr ""
"El http://opendata-ajuntament.barcelona.cat/[portal de dades obertes de "
"l’Ajuntament] està basat en el programari de portal dades de codi obert  "
"https://ckan.org/[CKAN]. Aquest producte és  http://docs.ckan.org/en/latest/"
"extensions/plugin-interfaces.htm[fàcilment] extensible mitjançant plugins o "
"extensions i durant el desenvolupament del nou portal va ser necessari tant "
"modificar una extensió ja existent (això es correspondria amb l'<<use-case-"
"adaptation, Escenari Adaptació>>) com crear-ne de noves."

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:145
#, no-wrap
msgid "`NewProduct` Use-case"
msgstr "Escenari `NouProducte`"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:149
msgid ""
"When there is no component or combination of components available that "
"satisfy a specific need, a new product has to be developed.  This product "
"may be based on other, already existing components, such as frameworks, "
"libraries, database management systems, etc."
msgstr ""
"Quan no es troba cap component o combinació de components que satisfan una "
"determinada necessitat, s’ha d’encarregar la implementació d’un producte nou."
" Aquest producte pot basar-se en altres components preexistents, com "
"frameworks, biblioteques, gestors de bases de dades, etc."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:151
#, no-wrap
msgid "Decidim.Barcelona"
msgstr "Decidim.Barcelona"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:157
msgid ""
"https://decidim.org/[Decidim] is a participative democracy tool for cities "
"and organisations.  From the outset, its development was sponsored by "
"Barcelona City Council, although other organisations that use it are now "
"beginning to contribute resources.  It is based on the website development "
"framework http://rubyonrails.org/[Ruby on Rails].  This framework greatly "
"facilitates the development of new website applications but these do not "
"merely consist of integrating and configuring components."
msgstr ""
"El https://decidim.org/[Decidim] és una eina de democràcia participativa per "
"ciutats i organitzacions. El desenvolupament va estar patrocinat des de "
"l’inici per l’Ajuntament de Barcelona, tot i que ara més organitzacions que "
"l’utilitzen comencen a aportar-hi recursos. Es basa en el framework per "
"desenvolupament web http://rubyonrails.org/[Ruby on Rails]. Aquest framework "
"facilita molt el desenvolupament de noves aplicacions web, però aquestes no "
"consisteixen simplement en una integració i configuració de components."

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:160
msgid ""
"https://decidim.org/[Decidim]’s history is a little odd because it began "
"with an attempt to adapt existing software, https://github.com/consul/"
"consul[Consul].  Later it was necessary to make a fork from the original "
"software and, finally, it was decided to rewrite the program (improving the "
"modularity of the code, among other things)."
msgstr ""
"La història del https://decidim.org/[Decidim] és una mica rocambolesca "
"perquè inicialment es va intentar fer una adaptació d’un programari ja "
"existent, el https://github.com/consul/consul[Consul]. Més tard va ser "
"necessari fer un fork del programari original, i finalment es va optar per "
"reescriure de nou l’aplicació (millorant, entre d’altres, la modularitat del "
"codi)."

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:163
#, no-wrap
msgid "`Publication` Use-case"
msgstr "Escenari `Publicació`"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:167
msgid ""
"Barcelona City Council owns a lot of software that is currently in use but "
"which has never been published.  The specific measures and recommendations "
"for this use-case explain the additional checks that are necessary for "
"publishing, under licence, a software code that initially was not conceived "
"for free distribution."
msgstr ""
"L’Ajuntament de Barcelona és el propietari legal de molt codi que es troba "
"en ús actualment, però que mai ha estat publicat. Les mesures i "
"recomanacions específiques d’aquest escenari expliquen les comprovacions "
"addicionals necessàries per publicar, sota una llicència lliure, un codi que "
"no va ser inicialment pensat per distribuir lliurement."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:170
msgid ""
"There may be several reasons that might justify publishing a software "
"program, provided it meets certain quality requirements.  One possible "
"situation is you might want to launch a new development contract for "
"extending or adapting “ manner” an existing component (that would be the "
"equivalent of combining the <<use-case-adaptation, Adaptation Use-case>> and "
"the <<use-case-publication, Publication Use-case>>)."
msgstr ""
"Por haver-hi diferents raons que justifiquin la publicació d’un codi, sempre "
"que compleixi amb certs requisits de qualitat. Una possible situació és que "
"es vulgui iniciar un nou contracte de desenvolupament per estendre o adaptar "
"«en obert» un component ja existent (això equivaldria a una combinació del "
"l'<<use-case-adaptation, Escenari Adaptació>> i l'<<use-cas-publication, "
"Escenari Publicació>>)."

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:172
#, no-wrap
msgid "`Document` Use-case"
msgstr "Escenari `Document`"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:176
msgid ""
"Sometimes you may want to publish a document that has been drafted (or "
"commissioned) that might not be linked directly to a single software project."
"  Examples would be market studies, research projects, graphic design "
"elements (such as logos) and so on."
msgstr ""
"A vegades es vol fer públic un document que s’ha redactat (o que s’ha "
"encarregat) i que pot no estar directament vinculat amb un sol projecte de "
"programari. Es pot tractar d’estudis de mercat, treballs de recerca, "
"elements de disseny gràfic (com per exemple logotips), etc."

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:177
#, no-wrap
msgid "Tags for project stages and milestones"
msgstr "Etiquetes per a fases i moments dels projectes"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:181
msgid ""
"When classifying measures and recommendations, it is also worth taking into "
"account at what point they should be applied.  As a general rule, we could "
"say that technological projects go through the following stages:"
msgstr ""
"A l’hora de categoritzar les mesures i recomanacions també és interessant "
"tenir en compte en quin moment s’han d’aplicar. Com a regla general, podem "
"considerar que els projectes tecnològics passen per les següents fases:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:183
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Conception*: stage when a new need is detected and the idea of the project "
"arises, which usually includes drawing up a preliminary design and possibly "
"carrying out other preliminary studies.\n"
msgstr ""
"*Concepció:* fase en la que es descobreix una nova necessitat o sorgeix la "
"idea del projecte, i que normalment inclou l’elaboració d’un avantprojecte i "
"possiblement d’altres estudis previs.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:184
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Procurement*: drawing up the specifications for acquiring services "
"(development or other types of services).\n"
msgstr ""
"*Contractació*: redacció dels plecs per a l’adquisició de serveis (de "
"desenvolupament o d’una altra naturalesa).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:185
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Development*: creating the source code, documents and other tools, "
"including the infrastructure necessary for building them.\n"
msgstr ""
"*Desenvolupament*: creació del codi, documentació i d’altres artefactes, "
"incloent l’establiment de la infraestructura necessària per a la construcció "
"dels mateixos.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:186
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Putting into production*: deploying the service, including the possible "
"migration of data and processes from one or more previous systems.\n"
msgstr ""
"*Pas a producció*: desplegament del servei, incloent la possible migració de "
"dades i processos des d’un o més sistemes previs.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:187
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Exploitation*: stage which lasts throughout the useful life of the system "
"in production, including operational and maintenance tasks.\n"
msgstr ""
"*Explotació*: fase que s’estén durant tota la vida útil del sistema en "
"producció, incloent les tasques d’operació i manteniment.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:189
msgid ""
"Taking all this into account, the Guide uses the following tags to highlight "
"key project stages:"
msgstr ""
"Tenint en compte tot això, a la Guia es fan servir les següents etiquetes "
"per assenyalar moments destacats dels projectes:"

#. type: Table
#: modules/ROOT/pages/document-organization.adoc:206
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Tag\n"
"| Description\n"
"\n"
"| `Preliminary design`\n"
"| Measures to take into account when drawing up preliminary designs.\n"
"\n"
"| `Procurement`\n"
"| Measures to take into account when drawing up the service procurement "
"specifications.\n"
"\n"
"| `Day1`\n"
"| Measures to be applied from the first day of the development stage (see "
"the section ).\n"
"\n"
"| `Release`\n"
"| Measures to take into account when a new version of the product is "
"released.\n"
msgstr ""
"| Etiqueta\n"
"| Descripció\n"
"\n"
"| `Avantprojecte`\n"
"| Mesures a tenir en compte en la redacció del avantprojectes.\n"
"\n"
"| `Contractar`\n"
"| Mesures a tenir en compte en la redacció dels plecs per a la contractació "
"de serveis.\n"
"\n"
"| `Dia1`\n"
"| Mesures a aplicar des del primer dia d’inici de la fase de desenvolupament "
"(veure l’apartat Treballar en obert des del «dia 1»).\n"
"\n"
